    "JubileeWaxcapDisplayName": "Jubilee Waxcap",
    "JubileeWaxcapDescription": "A lilac or pink mushroom with a slimy cap. Inedible.",

    "BluePinkgillDisplayName": "Blue Pinkgill",
    "BluePinkgillDescription": "The blue colouring of the fruit body is due to azulene pigments; the spores give its gills a pink tint. The Māori name for the mushroom is werewere-kōkako, because its colour is similar to the blue wattle of the kōkako bird. Edibility unknown.",

    "TheSickenerDisplayName": "The Sickener",
    "TheSickenerDescription": "Also known as 'Brittlegills'. Eating this mushroom is not recommended as it will make one vomit.",

